Class CidBuilder

    Builder<IdGenerator>, Parent<AttachImageBuilder>

    public class CidBuilder
extends AbstractParent<AttachImageBuilder>
implements Builder<IdGenerator>
    Configures how images are attached to Emails. Image defined in a html must be referenced by a Content-ID (or CID) if the image is attached to the email. You can define how CIDs are generated.

    • Method Detail

      • generator

        public CidBuilder generator(IdGenerator generator)
        Image defined in a html must be referenced by a Content-ID (or CID) if the image is attached to the email. You can define how CIDs are generated by defining an IdGenerator.

        Use this method to provide custom CID generation strategy.

        Any call to this method preempts any other configuration.

        If this method is called several times, only the last provided value is used.

        If null value is provided, it disables custom generator.

        Parameters:
        generator - the cid generator
        Returns:
        this instance for fluent chaining

      • sequential

        public CidBuilder sequential()
        Image defined in a html must be referenced by a Content-ID (or CID) if the image is attached to the email. You can define how CIDs are generated by defining an IdGenerator.

        Enables basic sequential CID generation: 0, 1, 2, 3...

        Returns:
        this instance for fluent chaining
